       <tr>
         <td class="name">iconClass</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="null" name="iconClass">
        Icon class for the dialog.  The icon is displayed in the title
        bar on the left side.
      </span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈String〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">null</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">maxBtn</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="true" name="maxBtn">
        Provide a “maximize” button?  Note that this has no effect if
        the dialog is not resizable.
      </span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈boolean〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">true</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">quitBtn</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="false" name="quitBtn">
        Provide a “quit” button? (see below)
      </span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈Function,String〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">false</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">modal</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="false" name="modal">Make the dialog modal?</span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈boolean〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">false</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">moveDelay</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="5000" name="moveDelay">Delay displaying the dialog during drag'n'drop</span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈Number〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">5000</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">noShadows</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="false" name="noShadows">Don't display shadows?</span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈boolean〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">false</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">resizable</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="false" name="resizable">Allow dialog resize?</span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈boolean〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">false</td>
       </tr>
       <tr>
         <td class="name">title</td>
         <td class="doc"><span default="&#34;DlDialog&#34;" name="title">Dialog title</span>
</td>
         <td class="type">[<b>〈String〉</b>]</td>
         <td class="optional"></td>
         <td class="default">"DlDialog"</td>
       </tr>
     </table>
   </div>
     <div class="doc"><span>
        Use this class to create a dialog.  A dialog is
        <em>usually</em> a top-level container which allows the user
        to enter some data, and then disappears.  It's a window, in
        essence, which can be moved, resized or closed (or hidden —
        “minimized”).  You've seen many samples of it already—almost
        all samples that you can run in this interactive demo are
        creating a dialog to display their widgets.
<p/>
      </span>

     </div>
   </div>
